HEADWORD: Graff
<hw>Graff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>grafe</ets>,
<ets>greife</ets>, <ets>greive</ets>. Cf. <er>Margrave</er>.]</ety>
<def>A steward; an overseer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[A prince] is nothing but a servant, overseer, or
<qex>graff</qex>, and not the head, which is a title belonging only to
Christ.</q> <rj><qau>John Knox.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graff</ent>⟦br⟧

